## Como rodar o projeto ?

### 1. Instalar o docker
https://www.docker.com/

### 2. Instalar Beekeeper Studio (Community Edition)
https://github.com/beekeeper-studio/beekeeper-studio

### 3. Rodar o docker
`docker run -d --name nubble-database -p 5432:5432 -e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=123456 postgres`

### 4. Instalar dependências
`yarn`

### 5. Criar Banco de Dados
Conectar através do beekeeper studio e criar DB com o nome de `nubble_db_development`

### 6. Resetar banco de dados e rodar seeds

`yarn reset`

### Rodar o projeto
Criei o arquivo .env baseado no exemplo:

```
# App
PORT=3333
HOST=0.0.0.0
NODE_ENV=development
APP_KEY=nNXnQq0_HbeqMI3V2iibFcpfb_Ci2fJN
DRIVE_DISK=local
DB_CONNECTION=pg

# Database
PG_HOST=localhost
PG_PORT=5432
PG_USER=postgres
PG_PASSWORD=123456
PG_DB_NAME=nubble_db_development

```

`yarn dev`
### Links
URL da API
http://localhost:3333

URL da documentação
http://localhost:3333/docs
